Defendant Robert L Turner in court with Attorney Jeffrey J Guerard.  Defendant Robert L Turner in custody.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Ken L.  AS TO COUNT #1:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be TWELVE (12) years consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for SIX (6) years with credit for ONE (1) day time served.  Defendant shall serve SIX (6) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.

AS TO COUNT #2:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be TWO (2) years CONCURRENT to count #1.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for ONE (1) year.  Defendant shall serve ONE (1) year on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  

The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program AFTER THREE (3) YEARS OF CONFINEMENT.
The defendant is eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program AFTER THREE (3) YEARS OF CONFINEMENT.

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Random urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - Restitution set at ZERO;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements.  Court ordered monies taken by the Department of Correction from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance would be then be paid while on Extended Supervision.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against Defendant.

